{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_1765",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "67fa65ba66f1853dd600529d69aa5945a8e2c360",
  "pr_number": 1765,
  "issue_number": 1763,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Simultaneous player loss is scored as a WIN for one player instead of a DRAW (CR 104.4a / 704.3)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nWhen two or more players meet a loss condition in the same state-based-action check, the engine eliminates them **sequentially** and runs the game-over check **after each elimination**. The first elimination sees the other dying player still \"alive\" and latches `GameOver { winner: Some(other) }`; the second elimination's game-over check early-returns because the result is already set. The engine therefore declares a player who has *also* lost as the **winner**, when CR 104.4a mandates a **draw**.\n\nState-based actions are required to be performed **simultaneously as a single event** (CR 704.3). The engine violates this by interleaving the game-over check between individual eliminations.\n\nThe loss check collects all losers, then eliminates them one at a time (`crates/engine/src/game/sba.rs`):\n\n```rust\nfn check_player_life(state: &mut GameState, events: &mut Vec<GameEvent>, any_performed: &mut bool) {\n    let to_eliminate: Vec<PlayerId> = state.players.iter()\n        .filter(|p| !p.is_eliminated && !p.is_phased_out() && p.life <= 0)\n        .filter(|p| !player_has_cant_lose(state, p.id))\n        .map(|p| p.id)\n        .collect();\n\n    for loser in to_eliminate {\n        events.push(GameEvent::PlayerLost { player_id: loser });\n        super::elimination::eliminate_player(state, loser, events);  // <- runs check_game_over each iteration\n        *any_performed = true;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n`eliminate_player` runs `check_game_over` after every single elimination (`crates/engine/src/game/elimination.rs`), and `check_game_over` latches the result and early-returns once set:\n\n```rust\nfn check_game_over(state: &mut GameState, events: &mut Vec<GameEvent>) {\n    if state.match_phase != MatchPhase::InGame\n        || matches!(state.waiting_for, WaitingFor::GameOver { .. })   // <- early-return once latched\n    { return; }\n    let living: Vec<PlayerId> = state.players.iter().filter(|p| !p.is_eliminated).map(|p| p.id).collect();\n    ...\n    if living.len() <= 1 {\n        let winner = living.first().copied();   // <- the *other* still-dying player\n        state.waiting_for = WaitingFor::GameOver { winner };\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe same sequential-eliminate-then-check pattern is used by every SBA loss check \u2014 `check_player_life`, `check_draw_from_empty`, `check_poison_counters`, and `check_commander_damage` \u2014 so the bug applies to all loss conditions, and to simultaneity *across* conditions within a single SBA check (one player at 0 life while another has 10 poison).\n\n## What the CR requires\n\nVerified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`:\n\n- CR 704.3: \"\u2026the game checks for [SBA conditions]\u2026 All applicable state-based actions are performed **simultaneously as a single event**\u2026\"\n- CR 704.5a: \"If a player has 0 or less life, that player loses the game.\"\n- CR 104.4a: \"If all the players remaining in a game lose simultaneously, the game is a **draw**.\"\n\nSo when every remaining player meets a loss condition in one SBA event, the result is a draw (`winner: None`), not a win for any of them.\n\n## Failure mode (concrete example)\n\n2-player game, both players at 5 life. The active player resolves a symmetric effect \u2014 e.g. \"each player loses 5 life\" (drain mirror, mutual life payment, or a spell dealing 5 to each player). Both reach 0.\n\n- **Engine:** the next SBA check builds `to_eliminate = [P0, P1]`, eliminates P0 first \u2192 `check_game_over` sees P1 not-yet-eliminated \u2192 latches `GameOver { winner: Some(P1) }`; P1 is then eliminated but the result is frozen. **P1 is declared the winner.**\n- **CR 104.4a:** both remaining players lost simultaneously \u2192 **the game is a draw** (`winner: None`).\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Reduce all remaining players to a loss condition in a single SBA event (e.g. a symmetric \"each player loses N life\" that is lethal to both, or simultaneous lethal damage to each player).\n2. Observe the game-over result: the engine reports one of the dying players as the winner instead of a draw.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nWhen all remaining players meet a loss condition simultaneously in one SBA check, the game ends in a **draw** (`WaitingFor::GameOver { winner: None }`). When only some players lose, the survivors are determined from the post-event state (one survivor \u2192 that player wins).\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nPlayers are eliminated sequentially with the game-over check interleaved, so the first-processed survivor at the moment of the first elimination is crowned winner even though they also lose in the same event.\n\n## Affected code paths\n\n- `game/sba.rs`: `check_player_life`, `check_draw_from_empty`, `check_poison_counters`, `check_commander_damage` \u2014 all loop `eliminate_player` per loser.\n- `game/elimination.rs`: `eliminate_player` runs `check_game_over` after each elimination; `check_game_over` latches `GameOver` and early-returns once set.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- Perform all simultaneous SBA losses as a **single event** (CR 704.3): collect every player that meets *any* loss condition in the current SBA check, mark them all eliminated first (via the inner `do_eliminate`, which does not run the game-over check), and then run `check_game_over` **once** so it observes the true post-event living set \u2014 yielding a draw (`winner: None`) when no players remain and a correct single winner otherwise.\n- Apply across all four loss checks so cross-condition simultaneity (life + poison + empty-library + commander damage in one check) is also batched.\n- Add fail-on-revert coverage: two players reduced to \u22640 life in one SBA check ends the game as a draw; a single player at \u22640 life still yields the correct sole winner; and a mixed case (one at 0 life, one at 10 poison) is a draw.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-01T13:38:23.000Z",
